The paper deals with computational aspects of markets with production, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses linear complementarity problems (LCPs) and pivot algorithms, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses equilibria and rationality, which are topics in economic theory (cs.EC) and network economics (cs.NE).
